</P><P ID="3"><NG><HEAD>ELLENSBURG</HEAD></NG> - <NG><HEAD>Launching</HEAD></NG> <NG>a new <HEAD>era</HEAD></NG> <PG>of</PG> <NG>music <HEAD>education</HEAD></NG> and <NG>music <HEAD>performance</HEAD></NG>, <NG><HEAD>Central Washington University</HEAD></NG> <PG>in</PG> <NG><HEAD>Ellensburg</HEAD></NG> <VG>will open</VG> <NG>the <HEAD>doors</HEAD></NG> <PG>to</PG> <NG>its new</NG>, <NG>state-of-the-art music education <HEAD>building</HEAD></NG> <PG>on</PG> <NG><HEAD>Sunday, Oct. 3</HEAD></NG>.   "<NG>This magnificent <HEAD>structure</HEAD></NG> <VG>has been</VG> <PG>in</PG> <NG>the planning <HEAD>stages</HEAD></NG> <PG>for</PG> <NG>many <HEAD>years</HEAD></NG>," <VG>says</VG> <NG><HEAD>CWU President Jerilyn S. McIntyre</HEAD></NG>. "<RG>Now</RG>, <NG>it</NG> <VG>is</VG> <NG>a <HEAD>dream</HEAD></NG> <VG>come</VG> <JG>true</JG> <PG>for</PG> all <PG>of</PG> <NG>us</NG> and <NG>a fitting <HEAD>home</HEAD></NG> <PG>for</PG> <NG>our outstanding music <HEAD>program</HEAD></NG>."   The $29-million <NG>facility <HEAD>measures</HEAD></NG> <NG>approximately</NG> <NG><CARDINAL>70,000</CARDINAL> square <HEAD>feet</HEAD></NG> and <VG>features</VG> a 600-seat <NG>concert <HEAD>hall</HEAD></NG>, 150-seat <NG>recital <HEAD>hall</HEAD></NG>, <NG><CARDINAL>30</CARDINAL> practice <HEAD>rooms</HEAD></NG>, <NG><CARDINAL>four</CARDINAL> rehearsal <HEAD>rooms</HEAD></NG> and <NG>several <HEAD>classrooms</HEAD></NG> and <NG>faculty <HEAD>studios</HEAD></NG>.   <PG>Among</PG> <NG>its most impressive <HEAD>features</HEAD></NG> <VG>are</VG> <NG>a main <HEAD>entry</HEAD></NG> <PG>with</PG> <NG>high <HEAD>ceilings</HEAD> and tall <HEAD>windows</HEAD></NG> <PG>for</PG> <NG>natural <HEAD>light</HEAD></NG>, and <NG>a main performance <HEAD>hall</HEAD></NG> <PG>with</PG> <NG>VIP <HEAD>boxes</HEAD></NG>. <PG>In</PG> <NG><HEAD>addition</HEAD></NG>, <NG><HEAD>walls</HEAD></NG> and <NG><HEAD>ceilings</HEAD></NG> <PG>of</PG> <NG>rehearsal <HEAD>rooms</HEAD></NG> <VG>are tailored</VG> <PG>to</PG> <NG>pa